cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM. 

The paper addresses the problem of segmenting objects in images given natural language expressions, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper proposes a novel method that integrates recursive language processing and convolutional neural networks, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques, making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with multimodal data (images and language), which could also make cs.MM a possible sub-category.
